Definition.WordDefinition: Dimensional \Di*men"sion*al\, a. Pertaining to dimension. [1913 Webster]

dimensional adj 1: of or relating to dimensions 2: having dimension--the quality or character or stature proper to a person; "never matures as a dimensional character; he is pasty, bland, faceless"- Norman Cousins
